text: Sequence analysis confirms that the human H1N1 strain went extinct in 1957 , but was reintroduced in 1976 , apparently from a specimen frozen in the early 1950s . The resulting " frozen " lineage appeared less mutated compared to all other contemporary H1N1 strains ( i . e . , porcine strains and a few rare H1N1 strains appearing in humans but not derived from the frozen strain ) . Consistent with the genetic attenuation model , the frozen human H1N1 lineage disappeared in 2009 , and may now be extinct .
